<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<activity xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="act-1-4-decimal-parts">
    <statement>
        <p>
            Just like we often convert between inches and decimal feet, we often convert between minutes and decimal hours.
        </p>
        <ol marker="(a)">
            <li>
                <p>
                    Use the fact that 1 hour = 60 minutes to write down two unit conversion fractions:
                    <me>
                        1 = \dfrac{<fillin fill="2.54" /> \text{ hour}}
                                  {<fillin fill="1.00" /> \text{ minutes}}
                        \quad \text{and} \quad
                        1 = \dfrac{<fillin fill="2.54" /> \text{ minutes}}
                                  {<fillin fill="1.00" /> \text{ hour}}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Is 57 minutes closer to one hour or to half an hour? Explain your thinking.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Cameron studied for 7 hours and 57 minutes. Convert this time into decimal hours using one of your unit conversion fractions in part (a).
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Explain why 7 hours and 57 minutes is <em>not</em> the same as 7.57 hours.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
</activity>